Function Reference/the author url « WordPress Codex
-----------

This tag displays the [URL](/Glossary#URI_and_URL "Glossary") to the
Website for the author of a post. The **Website** field is set in the
user's profile
([Administration](/Administration_Panels "Administration Panels") \>
[Profile](/Administration_Panels#Your_Profile "Administration Panels")
\> [Your Profile](/Your_Profile_SubPanel "Your Profile SubPanel")). This
tag must be used within [The Loop](/The_Loop "The Loop").

Replace With
------------

-   [the\_author\_meta('user\_url')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

Usage
-----

`  <?php the_author_url(); ?> `

Parameters
----------

This tag does not accept any parameters.

Example
-------

Displays the author's URL as a link and the link text.

    <p>Author's web site: 
    <a href="<?php the_author_url(); ?>"><?php the_author_url(); ?></a></p>

Which displays as:

Author's web site:
[www.example.com](/Template_Tags/the_author_url#Example "Template Tags/the author url")

This example displays the author's name as a link to the author's web
site.

    <?php if (get_the_author_url()) { ?><a href="<?php the_author_url(); ?>"><?php the_author(); ?></a><?php } else { the_author(); } ?>

Change Log
----------

-   Since: 1.5.0
-   Deprecated: 2.8.0
-   Replace By:
    [the\_author\_meta('user\_url')](/Template_Tags/the_author_meta "Template Tags/the author meta")

